R‚Üê‚çôGitCommit ‚çôRA;‚çôCMD;‚çôT;‚çôTEMP;‚çôWS

‚çù Add a commit to this workspace's repository containing all
‚çù altered objects in the current workspace.  A short character
‚çù vector commit message ("Message" above) is required with
‚çù each commit.
‚çù
‚çù This call requires that the workspace state matches that of the
‚çù corresponding local text files (by running ]TOTXT).
‚çù
‚çù Returns an error message or the following upon success (#### is
‚çù the commit number):
‚çù
‚çù  Commit #### created successfully
‚çù
‚çù [TLDR: Updates local text files, creates local git commit]

‚çù Requires the user command ]TOTXT

‚çù Syntax: R‚Üê‚çôGitCommit [MSG] [TEMP] [PDIR]
‚çù    MSG: Message to attach to commit
‚çù   TEMP: Temp path for use by ‚çôCOMMAND
‚çù     WS: WS' parent directory

‚çù Update all txt files to match the current workspace:
 ‚çôT‚Üê‚éïUCMD 'TOTXT'
 (‚çôRA ‚çôTEMP ‚çôWS)‚Üê‚çôRA

‚çù Save the current workspace
‚çù ‚éïSAVE (1+‚ç¥‚çôWS)‚Üì‚éïWSID ‚çù No, this would save all of the user command fns too
‚çù Consider using ]XSAVE on the objects (not the ucmds ones) in the ws

‚çù Build ‚éïCMD argument to pass to ‚àÜ_COMMAND
 ‚çôCMD‚Üê'git commit -m ',‚çôRA
‚çù Returns output from the ‚éïCMD call:
 R‚Üê‚çôTEMP ‚çôCOMMAND ‚çôWS ‚çôCMD
